{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we look at eye-tracking emotional-relevant features that can be applied to human-robot interactions.",
    "Facial Expression RecognitionFacial expressions are an effective nonverbal communication method for conveying emotional information among humans [114,115].",
    "Additionally, they are reflective of various human emotions and thoughts [116][117][118].",
    "Consequently, countries across the globe share a high level of agreement in identifying emotions through facial expressions [119].",
    "Recent research has even demonstrated that sixteen facial expressions occur in similar contexts worldwide, showcasing the universality of these expressions [114]."
  ]
}